HEADWORD: Tribromphenol
<hw>Tri`brom*phe"nol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A colorless crystalline substance
(<chform>C6H3OBr3</chform>) prepared by the reaction of carbolic acid
with bromine. The predominant isomer is 2,4,6-tribromophenol; -- called
also <altname>bromol</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

